  achieved v_inf ~ 1073 m/s — further headroom via finer Phase-A grid,
  raan_e sweep, t1/dv0 co-optimization, lower-energy (longer) returns.
Architecture: 3 impulses within spec — prograde raise to 1.2-1.5e9 m
  apogee (only +70-90 m/s over Hohmann), solar tide raises perigee to
  ~Moon distance + free plane change, small midcourse at apogee targets
  tangential arrival at target-orbit perilune, capture via
  solve_arrival_eccentric. Key methodological fix vs earlier failures
  (Tier-0, radius-only DC): optimize dv1 against alignment-aware capture
  proxy then EXACT dv2 (solve_arrival_eccentric inside NM objective);
  radius-only targeting gives steep 2.3 km/s encounters and loses.
Capacity discount: does NOT kill the lever for dT<=120d.
  Measured-anchor fleet model (v_inf=1073, dT=100d):
    current idD assignment: 197/302 transfers win, fleet +62k kg
    with idD re-matching:   295/302 win, fleet +128k kg
